48
00:06:17,008 --> 00:06:22,003
Grabbing the ball and release it.

49
00:06:22,003 --> 00:06:25,007
Look, it swings well.

50
00:06:25,008 --> 00:06:28,002
This is a pendulum.

51
00:06:28,002 --> 00:06:31,004
Actually, the pendulum we're using is special.

52
00:06:31,005 --> 00:06:35,008
The weight at the end is a powerful magnet.

53
00:06:37,006 --> 00:06:41,004
If we bring it close to a clip.

54
00:06:41,004 --> 00:06:45,002
it sticks to it firmly.

55
00:06:45,003 --> 00:06:54,000
♪
～


56
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:59,006
But here we have prepared an aluminum plate.

57
00:06:59,006 --> 00:07:02,002
And to this

58
00:07:07,003 --> 00:07:09,004
it doesn't stick at all.

59
00:07:09,005 --> 00:07:12,007
Magnets don't stick to aluminum.

60
00:07:12,007 --> 00:07:15,008
Now this is the problem.

61
00:07:15,008 --> 00:07:19,008
The aluminum plate that this magnet will not stick to

62
00:07:19,009 --> 00:07:23,008
we place it on the desk.

63
00:07:23,008 --> 00:07:28,000
And we separate the magnet from it.

64
00:07:28,001 --> 00:07:33,008
If we do this how will the pendulum swing?

65
00:07:33,008 --> 00:07:38,001
1. It will go slower than the case with no plate.

66
00:07:38,001 --> 00:07:40,001
and stop.

67
00:07:40,002 --> 00:07:44,009
2. Just the opposite. It will go faster and not stop at all.

68
00:07:44,009 --> 00:07:50,004
３｡
3. It will swing the same as if there were no plate.

69
00:07:50,004 --> 00:07:54,009
Well then what will happen?
We'll present the anser at the end of the program.

